SUMMARY:In-depth monitoring for Openstack services
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20180521T212000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20180521T220000Z
UID:20672@openstacksummitboston2017
DESCRIPTION:In 2014\, Ontario Institute for Cancer Research in Toronto\, C
 anada started building the Cancer Genome Collaboratory\, an OpenStack envi
 ronment designed for large scale cancerresearch projects. The cloud provid
 ing 2600 cores and 7.3 PB of object storage is now home to 90 users and 35
  research projects from four continents\, and in August 2017 it started a 
 cost recovery phase in order to maintain the sustainability of the project
 .\nIn this talk we will present our environment and focus on how a team of
