BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Open Stack and NVMe-over-Fabrics - Network connected SSDs with loc
 al performance
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20180522T171500Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20180522T175500Z
UID:21869@openstacksummitboston2017
DESCRIPTION:NVMe-over-Fabrics (NVMe-oF) enables low latency access over RD
 MA to remote NVMe-attached storage. This makes it a key enabler for disagg
 regated storage and NVMe pooling in data centers – architectures that dr
 ive increased efficiency. Intel\, Mellanox and Mirantis joined forces to e
 nable NVMe-oF in Openstack Cinder and Nova. Come join us to hear about the
  basics of NVMe-oF and its upcoming implementation in Rocky\, with kernel 
 LVM and SPDK LVOL based SDS backends.
LOCATION:Vancouver Convention Centre West - Level Two - Room 212
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:How Vault Systems created a secure OpenStack platform to bring gov
 ernment entities to the cloud
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20180522T180000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20180522T182000Z
UID:21874@openstacksummitboston2017
DESCRIPTION:If you’re going to help government entities to move to the c
 loud\, you must deliver a flexible and standards-based platform that meets
  strict security requirements. See how Vault built a fully redundant\, bla
 zing fast 100G network to the node\, utilizing DevOps philosophies and lev
 eraging Cumulus Networks and Mellanox. With this solution\, they can now a
 utomate switch provisioning while reducing the cost of network maintenance
 \, all while obtaining the flexibility they require to build a tailored so
 lution\, along with contributing security elements back to the OpenStack c
